where ğ¿(Â·, Â·) is the average of a pre-specified loss (e.g., cross-entropy) over all user-item pair, and ğ‘‡ = 1&ğ¶ = 0&ğ‘Œ = 0 equals to 1 only when the sample has observation (ğ‘‡ = 1, ğ¶ = 0, ğ‘Œ = 0), and equals to 0 otherwise. By adopting a similar view to the remaining identification formulas in Section 3.2, both models are jointly trained by minimizing the counterfactual stratification-task loss
